{"chunk_id": "8d70e13a-6851-4b65-862b-1554ba5427da", "source_database": "ICMR", "document_title": "ICMR_NIN_Dietary_Guidelines_Real.pdf", "publication_version": "Latest", "chunk_sequence_number": 148, "content_type": "Medical Guideline", "language": "English", "text": "/ butter/ vanaspati Rationale: /c233Fats/oils have high energy value and induce satiety. /c233Fats provide energy, essential fatty acids and promote absorption of fat-soluble vitamins. /c233Fats are precursors of biologically-active compounds in the body. /c233Diets that provide excess of calories, fats and cholesterol elevate blood lipids (cholesterol and triglycerides) and promote blood clotting. /c233Excessive fat in the diet increases the risk of obesity, heart disease, stroke and cancer. /c233Ill effects of excess dietary fats are initiated early in life. Cooking oils (liquid) and solid fats together are referred to as fats. Fats contribute to texture, flavor and taste and increase the palatability of the diet. Fats are essential for meeting some of the nutritional needs like", "embedding": [-0.02247215248644352, -0.07342670857906342, -0.0022366896737366915, 0.03042222373187542, 0.07086405903100967, 0.03060634806752205, -0.08243794739246368, 0.029717084020376205, 0.02357088401913643, -0.09892617911100388, -0.0448576994240284, -0.07108386605978012, -0.07273352146148682, -0.12842780351638794, 0.03161267936229706, -0.08161716908216476, 0.10045666247606277, 0.022850947454571724, -0.04825323820114136, -0.023200849071145058, 0.05485960841178894, -0.06189015880227089, 0.03562581166625023, 0.037695616483688354, -0.03540925681591034, 0.029498888179659843, 0.07271251082420349, -0.07497143000364304, -0.06500165164470673, -0.02092217281460762, 0.040674127638339996, -0.04442073032259941, -0.006536470260471106, -0.08041761815547943, -0.10027150809764862, -0.04286038875579834, -0.03469883278012276, -0.03454984351992607, -0.06292387843132019, -0.03204390034079552, 0.017000814899802208, -0.10546401888132095, 0.01